  "prompt": "How I recover my Facebook password?",
  "response": "Recovering your Facebook password can be done by following these steps:\n\n1. **Navigate to the Login Page**: Go to the Facebook login page by visiting www.facebook.com.\n\n2. **Locate the Forgot Password Link**: Below the password field, click on the link that says \"Forgot Password?\"\n\n3. **Identify Your Account**: You\u2019ll be prompted to enter the email address, phone number, or username associated with your account. If you don't remember what you used, try each one you can think of.\n\n4. **Choose Recovery Method**: Facebook will present you with options to receive a password reset link or code via email, SMS, or through another recovery method you've set up.\n\n5. **Enter Code or Click Link**: Once you receive the code or link, enter the code on the Facebook website (if provided) or click the reset link.\n\n6. **Set New Password**: Follow the on-screen instructions to enter a new password. Make sure it\u2019s something secure and unique.\n\n7. **Log In**: Use your new password to log in to your account.\n\nIf you face any difficulty or can\u2019t access the email/phone number associated with your account, you might need to go through Facebook's account recovery process where you'll validate your identity through other means, such as answering security questions or identifying friends' photos.\n\nIf these steps don't work or you need more assistance, you can visit Facebook's Help Center or contact Facebook support.\n\nRemember to always use a strong, unique password for your accounts and enable two-factor authentication for added security.",
